<RefNameDiv>
<RefName><command>mgr-sync</command></RefName>
<RefPurpose>
Management utility for adding, syncing, and enabling SUSE Customer Center channels.
</RefPurpose>
</RefNameDiv>

<RefSynopsisDiv>
<Synopsis>
    <cmdsynopsis>
        <command>mgr-sync</command>
    </cmdsynopsis>
</Synopsis>
</RefSynopsisDiv>

<RefSect1><Title>Description</Title>

<para>
  The (<emphasis>mgr-sync</emphasis>) is a utility that allows you to work
  with SUSE Customer Center for adding or syncing of products and channels.
  As well as enabling and refreshing SCC data.  This tool requires that
  SCC is enabled by running "mgr-sync enable-scc".
</para>
</RefSect1>

<RefSect1><Title>Options</Title>
<variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--help</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Display usage and exit.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>--version</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Prints the version.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>-v, --verbose</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Enable verbose output.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>-s,  --save-config</term>
        <listitem>
            <para>Save the configuration to the local dot file.</para>
        </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
      #under list
    <varlistentry>
        <term>list</term>
        <listitem>
          <term>channel | channels</term>
          <para>channel or channels to list channels.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <term>product | products</term>
            <para>product or products to list products.</para>
        </listitem>    
        <listitem>
            <term>credentials</term>
            <para>credentials to list credentials</para>
        </listitem>    
        <listitem>
            <term>-e , --expand</term>
            <para>Expands all children if parent is not subsribed.</para>
        </listitem>    
        <listitem>
            <term>-f FILTER , --filter FILTER</term>
            <para>Filter the ouput by what contains the filter word.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>--no-optional</term>
            <para>Don't show optional channels.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>-c, --compatct</term>
            <para>Compact output.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>--from-mirror</term>
            <para>URL of a local mirror like SMT.  Only used for downloading RPMs.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>-h, --help</term>
            <para>Show help menu for this command.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>--primary</term>
            <para>Desginate SCC organization credentials as primary.</para>
        </listitem>     
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
        <term>add</term>
        <listitem>
          <term>channel, channels CHANNEL</term>
          <para>Add and sync channel.  It will also accept multiple channels.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <term>product, products PRODUCT</term>
            <para>Add and sync mandatory channels for a product.</para>
        </listitem>    
        <listitem>
            <term>credentials</term>
            <para>To add credentials.</para>
        </listitem>    
        <listitem>
            <term>-c, --compatct</term>
            <para>Compact output.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>--from-mirror</term>
            <para>URL of a local mirror like SMT.  Only used for downloading RPMs.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>-h, --help</term>
            <para>Show help menu for this command.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>--primary</term>
            <para>Designate SCC organization credentials as primary.</para>
        </listitem>     
    <varlistentry>
        <term>refresh</term>
        <listitem>
          <term>--refresh-channels</term>
          <para>Schedule a refresh of all installed channels.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <term>--from-mirror</term>
            <para>URL of a local mirror like SMT.  Only used for downloading RPMs.</para>
        </listitem>     
        <listitem>
            <term>-h, --help</term>
            <para>Show help menu for this command.</para>
        </listitem>     
     <varlistentry>
        <term>delete</term>
        <listitem>
          <term>TARGET</term>
          <para>SCC orginization credentials to delete.</para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <term>-h, --help</term>
            <para>Show help menu for this command.</para>
        </listitem>     
    </varlistentry>
    </varlistentry>
  </varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</RefSect1>

<refsect1><title>Examples</title>
<simplelist>
  <member><command>mgr-sync enable-scc</command></member>
  <member><command>mgr-sync channel add test-channel-name</command></member>
  <member><command>mgr-sync list -e</command></member>
  <member><command>mgr-sync product add --from-mirror http//smtmirror.com product-name</command></member>
 </simplelist>
</refsect1>

